-- UBS Hires Ex-Credit Suisse Treasury Trader Sheehan as a Managing Director
-- Daniel Kruger
-- 2010-08-02T19:08:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-02/ubs-hires-ex-credit-suisse-treasury-trader-sheehan-as-a-managing-director.html

          
          
             UBS AG, one of the 18 primary dealers
that trade with the Federal Reserve, said it hired John Sheehan,
the former head of Treasury trading at Credit Suisse Group AG.  
 Sheehan will join as a managing director in September and
work on the firm’s Treasury trading desk in Stamford,
Connecticut, said  Doug Morris , a UBS spokesman. He will report
to  Jay Merchant,  who heads the desk.  
 Sheehan had run Credit Suisse’s trading desk in New York
for the past three years until June when, he was succeeded by
 James O’Brien  from Toronto-Dominion Bank.  
 Credit Suisse didn’t return calls seeking comment.  
